Package examblock.model

Interface ManageableListItem

All Known Implementing Classes:
Exam, Room, Session, Student, Subject, Unit, Venue
public interface ManageableListItem
Interface for items managed by ListManager. All items must implement this interface to be stored in a ListManager, ensuring they provide a unique identifier and methods for persistence and display.

  • Method Details

    • getFullDetail

      String getFullDetail()
      Returns a string containing enough information to reconstruct the item during deserialization (e.g., streaming in from disk).
      Returns:
      a string representation of the object's state

    • toTableRow

      default Object[] toTableRow()
      Returns an array of values suitable for display in a view model, such as a JTable. This method provides basic column data. This interface method should provide a default implementation that returns an empty array.
      Returns:
      an array of objects for insertion into a table

    • toLongTableRow

      default Object[] toLongTableRow()
      Returns an extended array of values for display in a view model, such as a JTable. This method is optional and provides additional column data. This interface method should provide a default implementation that returns an empty array.
      Returns:
      an array of objects for insertion into a table

    • getId

      default String getId()
      Returns a string that uniquely identifies this object. Used by Registry for lookup and ensuring uniqueness. This interface method should provide a default implementation that returns an empty string.
      Returns:
      the unique identifying string, or an empty string if not applicable
